6	//! Memory operation conversion: `dialect-mir` → LLVM dialect.
7	//!
8	//! Converts `dialect-mir` memory operations to their LLVM dialect equivalents.
9	//!
10	//! # Operations
11	//!
12	//! | MIR Operation        | LLVM Operation(s)                 | Description                  |
13	//! |----------------------|-----------------------------------|------------------------------|
14	//! | `mir.load`           | `llvm.load`                       | Load from pointer            |
15	//! | `mir.store`          | `llvm.store`                      | Store to pointer             |
16	//! | `mir.ref`            | `llvm.alloca` + `llvm.store`      | Materialize aggregate in mem |
17	//! | `mir.ptr_offset`     | `llvm.getelementptr`              | Pointer arithmetic           |
18	//! | `mir.shared_alloc`   | `llvm.global` + `llvm.addressof`  | Static shared memory         |
19	//! | `mir.extern_shared`  | `llvm.global` + `llvm.addressof`  | Dynamic shared memory        |
20	//!
21	//! # Shared Memory
22	//!
23	//! ## Static Shared Memory (`SharedArray<T, N, ALIGN>`)
24	//!
25	//! Each static shared memory allocation gets a unique global symbol (`__shared_mem_N`).
26	//! Multiple allocations in the same or different kernels each have their own symbol
27	//! with their own size and alignment.
28	//!
29	//! ## Dynamic Shared Memory (`DynamicSharedArray<T, ALIGN>`)
30	//!
31	//! Dynamic shared memory uses a symbol for each function that owns an access
32	//! (`__dynamic_smem_{function_name}`).
33	//! Key characteristics:
34	//!
35	//! - **Per-owner symbols**: Each function containing an access gets an extern symbol
36	//! - **Pre-computed alignment**: A pre-pass combines the owner's body alignment with
37	//!   the strongest launch-contract marker that can reach it
38	//! - **Single runtime pool per launch**: The symbols refer to dynamic shared memory
39	//!   sized by `shared_mem_bytes` at launch
40	//!
41	//! ### PTX Output Example
42	//!
43	//! ```ptx
44	//! ; Kernel with 128-byte aligned dynamic shared memory
45	//! .extern .shared .align 128 .b8 __dynamic_smem_my_kernel[];
46	//!
47	//! ; Another kernel with 16-byte aligned (default)
48	//! .extern .shared .align 16 .b8 __dynamic_smem_other_kernel[];
49	//! ```
